Fix out-of-bounds when ParamActive::whichTrial is called with sz<=1.

The original logic returned -1 as soon as the first registered trial did
not overlap, whenever the queried range was 1 byte or less.  That's wrong:
when sz<=1 the endaddr overlap check is trivially redundant (endaddr ==
addr), so we should simply continue to the next trial instead of bailing
out.  Returning -1 prematurely makes callers index a vector with -1,
crashing under _GLIBCXX_ASSERTIONS (or causing UB / heap corruption
otherwise).  See rizinorg/rz-ghidra#385.

diff --git a/src/decompiler/fspec.cc b/src/decompiler/fspec.cc
--- a/src/decompiler/fspec.cc
+++ b/src/decompiler/fspec.cc
@@ -1984,7 +1984,7 @@ int4 ParamActive::whichTrial(const Address &addr,int4 sz) const
 {
   for(int4 i=0;i<trial.size();++i) {
     if (addr.overlap(0,trial[i].getAddress(),trial[i].getSize())>=0) return i;
-    if (sz<=1) return -1;
+    if (sz<=1) continue;
     Address endaddr = addr + (sz-1);
     if (endaddr.overlap(0,trial[i].getAddress(),trial[i].getSize())>=0) return i;
   }
